Hi!

`@ngtools/webpack` performs a ngcc run check to determine if an initial execution is required. It looks for `yarn.lock` or `package-lock.json` to run this check. But our project uses [pnpm](https://pnpm.io/), which has `pnpm-lock.yaml`. And `@ngtools/webpack` thinks it is first time build and runs 'ngcc'.

We are using version `12.2.14`, but I see this code still [there](https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/blob/master/packages/ngtools/webpack/src/ngcc_processor.ts): 

```js
    try {
      let lockData;
      let lockFile = 'yarn.lock';
      try {
        lockData = readFileSync(path.join(projectBasePath, lockFile));
      } catch {
        lockFile = 'package-lock.json';
        lockData = readFileSync(path.join(projectBasePath, lockFile));
      }

      let ngccConfigData;
      try {
        ngccConfigData = readFileSync(path.join(projectBasePath, 'ngcc.config.js'));
      } catch {
        ngccConfigData = '';
      }
```
